           <div type="translation" source="bib:Chhom2011_01"><!-- kuch: The term 'slave' should be understood as 'servant'. -->
 	<p n="1-14">Village of Cralaḥ : Gho Kañjāṅ, Gho Kaṁvis, Gho Kandhan, Gho Kaṁvai, Gho Bhavitavya, Gho Kanhen, Gho Thgap, Gho Kañcū, Gho Krau, Gho Cradit, Gho <gap reason="lost"/>, Gho Sajjana, Gho Caṁlau, Gho Kaṁvrau, Gho Agat, Gho Jaidasa, Gvāl <gap reason="lost"/>, Gvāl Krau, Tai Kandai, Tai Kandhi, Tai Kantej, Tai Thkep, Tai Malaya, Tai Kapas, <gap reason="lost"/>, Tai Kan-aṁ, Tai Kanduc, Tai Kañjaṅ, Tai Śaṅkā, Tai Kañcyas, Tai <gap reason="lost"/>, Tai Kanso, Tai Kaṁvi, Lap Phtal, Lap Kaṁpit, Lap Khnap. Total: 16 male slaves <supplied reason="explanation"><foreign>gho</foreign></supplied>, 2 animal keepers <supplied reason="explanation"><foreign>gvāl</foreign></supplied>, 15 female slaves <supplied reason="explanation"><foreign>tai</foreign></supplied>, 3 male slaves <supplied reason="explanation"><foreign>lap</foreign></supplied>; grand total 36.</p>
              <p n="14-19">Village of Mahanasa: Gho Kansip, Gho Kan-as, Gho Kaṁvi, Gho Bhāva, Gvāl Kañcū, Gho Kandhi, Tai <gap reason="lost"/>, Tai Pandan, Tai Kañcan accompanied by a baby boy <supplied reason="explanation"><foreign>si pau</foreign></supplied>, Tai Gandha, Lap Kaṁput. Total: 5 male slaves <supplied reason="explanation"><foreign>gho</foreign></supplied>, an animal keeper, 4 female slaves <supplied reason="explanation"><foreign>tai</foreign></supplied>, a male slave <supplied reason="explanation"><foreign>lap</foreign></supplied> and a baby boy; grand total 12.</p>
              <p n="19-24">Village of Stuk Srek: Gho <gap reason="lost"/> Kaṁpañ, Gho Taṁpar, Tai <gap reason="lost"/>, Tai Pāṇa, Tai Chke, <gap reason="lost"/> Tai Nagha. Total <gap reason="lost"/> a baby; grand total <gap reason="lost"/></p>
